article.headline: Indiana St. 76, Bradley 66
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Gabe Moore scored 27 points, including a perfect 14 of 14 free throws, as Indiana State beat Bradley 76-66 Tuesday night in the Missouri Valley Conference. Indiana State (11-13, 6-8 MVC) shot just 44 percent from the field but was 28-of-31 (90.3 percent) from the line. The Sycamores outrebounded the Braves 39-32 and led 33-32 at the break. Marico Stinson chipped in 14 and Isiah Martin 10 for Indiana State, whose bench outscored Bradley's 16-10. Andrew Warren led Bradley (14-12, 7-7) with 17. Daniel Ruffin had 16 points and seven assists, and Jeremy Crouch scored 11 for the Braves.
